memsched

For job scheduling on embedded or low-powered systems


* optional persistance to sqlite3 (so not mem-)

A `job` is a request for work. A job can 
contain N `tasks` which themselves are atomic processes.
Each task is a sequential step to complete the job. 

A `resource` is something provided by the `node`, or 
compute executing this work, and the schduler will 
optimise task runs on these resources to fufill them.


